Updates for 2025-06-12
Spoiler 
Removed Patch Notes:
Horned Scarab of Glittering now grants increased Item Quantity up to 50% (previously 100%).

Updated Patch Notes:
Old:
Horned Scarab of Glittering now has Players in Area gain increased Item Rarity for each Monster slain recently, up to 400% (from every 4 seconds and up to 200%. No longer has Item Quantity)
New:
Horned Scarab of Glittering now has Players in Area gain increased Item Rarity for each Monster slain, up to 400%, decaying over time (from up to 200%. No longer grants Item Quantity. Note the decay rate is no longer described as recently, as it was never over 4 seconds but was 20 seconds from the maximum value)

New Patch Notes:
Player Balance
Changed how additional party members scale the quantity and rarity of items the player finds.
We now drop +100% more of certain Item classes like Currency and Gold as they are valuable for all players, whereas items like Armour and Weapons scale at much lower amounts. The result of this is that when in larger parties you see less non-unique equipment, and more things you actually want.
We no longer increase Rarity per player in a party but we increase the number of Uniques specifically, this will result in the same number of Unique Items per party member as before.

Endgame Changes
The Antagonist's modifier on Tier 17 maps now grants Rare Monsters an additional Modifier (from 2 additional). This does not affect existing items
Reduced the amount of increased Pack Size granted by Tier 17 Map Modifiers that specifically augment Pack Size. Values have been lowered from 25% to 15%. This does not affect existing items with these modifiers.
Abyss Scarab of Multitudes now grants Abysses in Area spawn 50% increased Monsters (from 75%).
Horned Scarab of Glittering now has Players in Area gain increased Item Rarity for each Monster slain recently, up to 400% (from every 4 seconds and up to 200%. No longer has Item Quantity)
Resplendent Tempests from the Scarab of Radiant Storms no longer grants Item Quantity bonuses and has had an increase to the Item Rarity bonus on players.
Corrupted Growths in Crimson Iron Ore Encounters are now Normal rarity monsters (previously Unique rarity). These were always just intended to be a monster spawner as opposed to an actual reward source.
Split the existing Modifier that granted increased Quantity and Rarity of Items found in Area from Cleansing and Tangle Influence Altars into two separate ones:
10-20% increased Quantity of Items found in this Area
15-30% increased Rarity of Items found in this Area

Sanctum Rewards Changes
The Sanctum room rewards which allow you to defer currency to the end of the Floor or End of the Sanctum now have a lower chance to contain high tier currency (like Divine Orbs) and on floor three those currency items no longer appear with stack sizes greater than one. The ease of completing Sanctum relative to the rewards is mismatched and this puts it more in line. We are intending to do a grander pass to the rewards and content of Sanctum in a future expansion where we will also be adding an exclusive reward to Sanctum to give it more identity instead of exclusively producing raw currency.

Recombinator Changes
The Recombinator, when using the now Unpredictable Recombination method will result in fewer modifiers on the item on average if the input items were using many modifiers that cannot normally roll on the item, for example Veiled Modifiers or Essence Modifiers. This should result in the very top-end becoming less optimal for creating the best items, without affecting the average use cases. This change was made after the Livestream Q&A based on feedback with the intention of bringing down the top end Recombinator power without affecting it for the majority of users, this doesn't change the maximum power it can produce, just makes it more difficult to achieve.

Updates for 2025-06-11
Spoiler 
New Patch Notes:
The "Item drops on Death if Equipped by an Animated Guardian" Crafting Option has been removed. This modifier on existing items is no longer functional.
"Item drops on Death if Equipped by an Animated Guardian" no longer can appear as a Synthesized Modifier on Body Armours.
Physical Attack Damage Leeched as Life Modifiers on Weapons now scale from 2% to 4.5% (from 0.2-1.2). The level life leech modifiers appear on weapons has been lowered from level 50 to level 20.
The Physical Attack Damage Leeched as Mana Modifier on Weapons is now 2.6% to 3.2% (from 0.2-0.4%)
Physical Attack Damage Leeched as Life/Mana Essence Modifiers and Crafting Bench Modifiers on Weapons have been adjusted accordingly.

Updates for 2025-06-10
Spoiler 
New Patch Notes
A new Hasty Demise cluster has been added to the north-west of the Witch's starting location. Hasty Demise provides 30% increased Damage Over Time with Spell Skills, 8% increased Cast Speed, and 10% reduced Skill Effect Duration.
A new Harsh Lessons cluster has been added to the north-east of the Witch's starting location. Harsh Lessons provides +12% to Damage Over Time Multiplier with Spell Skills, and 20% reduced Duration of Ailments on You.
A new Arcane Retaliation cluster has been added to the north-west of the Witch's starting location. Arcane Retaliation provides 25% more Spell Damage if you've been Stunned while Casting Recently.
The Cold Passive Mastery that provided +1% to maximum Cold Resistance has been replaced with a new Mastery that provides +1% to Cold Damage over Time Multiplier for each 4% Overcapped Cold Resistance.
The Cold Passive Mastery that caused Enemies near targets you shatter to have 20% chance to be Covered in Frost has been replaced with a new Mastery that provides -30% to Fire Resistance, and +1 to level of all Cold Skill Gems.
The Caster Mastery that provided 25% more Spell Damage if you've been Stunned while casting Recently has been replaced with a new Mastery that causes you to Gain a Power Charge every second while Channelling a Spell.
The Caster Mastery that causes Final Repeat of Spells to have increased Area of Effect now has values of 40% (previously 30%).
The Staff Passive Mastery that provided 20% chance for Double Stun Duration has been replaced with a new Mastery that provides 5% increased maximum Mana per Blue Socket on equipped Staff, and 3% increased maximum Life per Red Socket on equipped Staff.

Occultist
The Vile Bastion Ascendancy Passive Skill no longer has "Regenerate 2% of Energy Shield per second for each Enemy you or your Minions have Killed Recently, up to 10% per second". It now grants 100 Energy Shield Regeneration per second (previously 40) and now has "Maximum Energy Shield is increased by Chance to Block Spell Damage".

Changes to existing Patch Notes:
Old: The Omeyocan Unique Boots now grant 20% increased Evasion Rating per 500 Maximum Mana, up to 200% (previously 10% per 500 up to 100%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
New: The Omeyocan Unique Boots now grant 20% increased Evasion Rating per 500 Maximum Mana (previously 10% per 500). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb. This stat was previously described as being capped at 100% increased Evasion Rating, but was never actually capped.

Updates for 2025-06-09
Spoiler 
Changes to existing Patch Notes:
Old: The Shaper of Winter Ascendancy Passive Skill no longer has 50% more Effect of Cold Ailments you inflict with Hits for which the highest Damage Type is Cold, Chills from your Hits always reduce Action Speed by at least 15%, or Your Chills can reduce Action Speed by up to a maximum of 40%. Instead, it now causes Enemies Chilled by your Hits lessen their Damage dealt by half of Chill Effect, and Enemies Chilled by your Hits have Damage taken increased by Chill Effect.

New: The Shaper of Winter Ascendancy Passive Skill no longer has 50% more Effect of Cold Ailments you inflict with Hits for which the highest Damage Type is Cold, or Chills from your Hits always reduce Action Speed by at least 15%. Instead, it now causes Enemies Chilled by your Hits to lessen their Damage dealt by half of Chill Effect.

Old: The following Divination Card has been temporarily disabled: Avian Pursuit. Existing Divination Cards cannot be turned in currently.

New: The Avian Pursuit Divination Card now awards 1,500 Vivid Lifeforce.

New Patch Notes:
Ambush Scarab now has Area contains 3 additional Strongboxes (previously 5).
Beyond Scarab of Haemophilia now has Beyond Portals in Area have 50% increased Merging Radius (previously 30%).
Apparition Shrine Buffs from the Domination Scarab of Apparitions now have a significantly lower chance for players to drop Influenced Items.
Breach Scarab of Resonant Cascades now grants Breach Monsters 50% more increased Reward for each Breach already opened.
Breach Scarab of Snares now has Breaches in Area have 3 to 5 additional Clasped Hands (previously 5 to 10) This change does not apply to Ruthless.
Cartography Scarab of Risk now has Area has 2 additional random Modifiers (previously 1 additional).
Divination Scarab of Plenty now has Area contains 6 to 10 additional Packs of Divination Touched Magic Monsters (previously 3).
Evolving Shrine Buffs from the Domination Scarab of Evolution now have double the chance to evolve defeated monsters.
Horned Scarab of Glittering now grants increased Item Quantity up to 50% (previously 100%).
Expedition Scarab of Verisium Powder has Expedition Encounters in Area have 50% increased number of Explosives (previously 20%).
Obelisks from the Harbinger Scarab of Obelisks now drop 66% more Currency Shards on average.
The Scarab of Monstrous Lineage now has a limit of 2 (previously 1).
Ritual Scarab of Wisps now has Wildwood Wisps grant 100% increased Tribute Gained to nearby Players (previously 70%).
Titanic Scarab now has Unique Monsters have 1% increased Toughness, Damage, Rarity and Quantity of items dropped per 1% increased Pack Size of Area (previously 2% increased Toughness, Damage, Rarity and Quantity of items dropped).
Titanic Scarab of Treasures now has Unique Monsters in Area have an additional Reward (previously 2 additional rewards).
The Horned Scarab of Awakening Imbued Crafting Options have also been adjusted:
Ambush: 300% increased chance for Strongboxes in Area to be Unique (previously 100%).
Breach: Area contains 3 additional Breaches (previously 2).
Delirium: Delirium Monsters in Area have 80% increased Pack Size.
Harbinger: Harbingers have a 40% chance to be replaced by a powerful Harbinger boss (previously 25%).
Ritual: 500% increased chance of Ritual Altars with special Rewards (previously 150%).
Torment: Area is haunted by 15 additional Tormented Spirits (previously 8).
Apparitions granted through the Domination Scarab of Apparitions shrines now deal substantially more damage.
The Actum Unique One Handed Axe now has 30-40% Critical Strike Chance for Hits with this Weapon (previously 20-30%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Admiral Unique Body Armour now has 120-200% increased Evasion and Energy Shield (previously 100-140%) and grants 10-25% chance to Freeze, Shock and Ignite (previously 5-10%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Allelopathy Unique Gloves now grant level 25 Blight (previously level 22). This change automatically affects existing items, but the level will display incorrectly unless a Divine Orb is used.
The Replica Allelopathy Unique Gloves now grant level 25 Wintertide Brand (previously level 22). This change automatically affects existing items, but the level will display incorrectly unless a Divine Orb is used.
The Brain Rattler Unique Two Handed Mace now has 100-130 to 360-430 added Physical Damage (previously 60-80 to 270-320). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Icicle Burst skill triggered by the Cameria's Avarice Unique One Handed Mace now has a cooldown of 0.3 seconds (from 0.5 seconds) and deals 200% of base and added damage (previously 150%).
The Daresso's Defiance Unique Body Armour now grants 2% of Attack Damage Leeched as Life (previously only Physical Attack Damage). This change automatically affects existing items.
The Enmity Divine and Yielding Mortality Unique Staves now have 225-265 to 315-385 added Physical Damage (previously 160-185 to 200-225) and +60-80% to Damage Over Time Multiplier for Bleeding from Critical Strikes (previously 30-40%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Divinity Buff granted by the Garb of the Ephemeral Unique Body Armour now grants 75% more Elemental Damage (previously 50%) and 25% less Elemental Damage taken (previously 20%).
The Grace of the Goddess Unique Wand now grants 10-50% of Physical Damage as Extra Lightning, Cold and Fire Damage (previously 10-30%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Facebreaker Unique Gloves now grant 600-1000% more Unarmed Physical Damage (previously 600-800%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Hand of Thought and Motion Unique Claw now grants 1-12 added Lightning Damage per 10 Dexterity (previously 1-10). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Hand of Wisdom and Action Unique Claw now grants 1-12 added Lightning Damage per 10 Intelligence (previously 1-10). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Kaom's Spirit Unique Gloves now Regenerates 1 Rage per second for every 200 Life Recovery per second from Regeneration (previously for every 300). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Kintsugi Unique Body Armour now has 160-220% increased Evasion Rating (previously 120-160%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Mark of the Doubting Knight Unique Dagger now has 20% reduced Attack Speed (previously 10%) and no longer has +6-10% to all Elemental Resistances, but now has 20-30% increased Critical Strike Chance and +30-40% to Global Critical Strike Multiplier. A Divine Orb will only change the Attack Speed of existing copies, if you're desperate to make this item worse.
The Null's Inclination Unique Bow now grants Minions 2% increased Damage per 5 Dexterity (previously 1). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Nuro's Harp Unique Bow now has 180-210 to 240-280 added Cold Damage (previously 120-140 to 180-210). It also now has 30-50% increased Effect of Chilled Ground (previously 40%). Existing items can receive these changes using a Divine Orb. It also now has 30-50% increased effect of Consecrated Ground, which does not affect existing items.
The Omeyocan Unique Boots now grant 20% increased Evasion Rating per 500 Maximum Mana, up to 200% (previously 10% per 500 up to 100%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Primordial Chain Unique Amulet now causes Golems to have 35-25% less Life and deal 35-25% less Damage (previously 45-35%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Queen's Decree Unique Two Handed Sword now has +1-2 to maximum Zombies, Skeletons and Spectres (previously +1). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Sporeguard Unique Body Armour now grants +29-43% Chaos Resistance (previously 17-23%) and causes enemies on Fungal Ground to explode for 10% of their maximum Life (previously 5%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Shield Shatter Skill granted by the Shattershard Unique Shield now deal 100% more damage but deals 40% less damage with Ailments. The lingering buff granted by the skill now grants 1-15 to 3-23 Added Spell Physical Damage per 1% Shield Quality (previously 1-10 to 2-16).
The Steelworm Unique Quiver now grants additional projectiles after consuming 8 Steel Shards (previously 12). This change automatically affects existing items.
The Soul taker Unique One Handed Axe now has 25-35% increased Attack Speed (from 20-25%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Soulwrest Unique Staff now triggers level 25 Summon Phantasm on corpse consumption (previously level 20). It also now grants Minions 90-102 to 132-156 additional Physical Damage (previously 45-51 to 66-78). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Void Shot Skill granted by the Voidfletcher Unique Quiver now deals 100% more Area Damage (previously 25%).
The Warrior's Legacy Unique Ring now only requires half as much distance between you and your previous location in order to permit the spirit strike to occur. This change automatically applies to existing items.
The Winds of Fate Unique Staff now has +100-150% to Critical Strike Multiplier (previously 100%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Wings of Entropy Unique Two Handed Axe now adds 150-200 to 330-400 Fire Damage in Main Hand (previously 75-100 to 165-200) and 151-199 to 331-401 Chaos Damage in Off Hand (previously 75-100 to 165-200). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Replica Wings of Entropy Unique Two Handed Axe now has 50-100% more Main Hand Attack Speed (previously 50-70%) and +10-20% to Off Hand Critical Strike Chance (previously 8-10%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Xirgil's Crank Unique Staff now grants +70-150 Energy Shield (previously 70-100) and a 25-35% chance for Energy Shield Recharge to start when you Block (previously 20%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Rhoa variant of the Yriel's Fostering Unique Body Armour now grants Projectile Attacks 100% chance to Maim on Hit while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 20%), and 10-20% increased Attack and Movement Speed while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 10-15%). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Ursa variant of the Yriel's Fostering Unique Body Armour now grants Projectile Attacks 100% chance to inflict Bleeding on Hit while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 20%), and adds 18-24 to 30-36 Physical Damage to Attacks while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 11-16 to 21-25). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.
The Snake variant of the Yriel's Fostering Unique Body Armour now grants Projectile Attacks 100% chance to Poison on Hit while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 20%), and adds 23-31 to 37-47 Chaos Damage to Attacks while you have a Bestial Minion (previously 13-19 to 23-29). Existing items can be updated using a Divine Orb.

Updates for 2025-06-06
Spoiler 
New Patch Notes:

Hexblast: Now has a 2 second Cooldown Time, with 3 Uses. Now has a base radius of 3.2 metres (previously 2.8), and the Spell's Cast Time is no longer added to its Cooldown if Triggered. Now has 150% more Damage with Hits if Enemy is Hexed (previously 100%), and 60% more Damage with Ailments if Enemy is Hexed (previously 40%).
Hexblast of Contradiction: Now has a 2 second Cooldown Time, with 3 Uses. Now has a base radius of 3.2 metres (previously 2.8), and the Spell's Cast Time is no longer added to its Cooldown if Triggered. Now has 240% more Damage with Hits if Enemy is Hexed (previously 150%), and 90% more Damage with Ailments if Enemy is Hexed (previously 40%).
The Executioner Monster modifier's Aura once again does not prevent minions from recovering life.



We really hope you enjoy Path of Exile: Secrets of the Atlas. Thanks for your support!